Package com.msasc.lib.util.launch

Class Argument

java.lang.Object
com.msasc.lib.util.launch.Argument
public class Argument extends Object
Startup or command line argument to help the management, i.e. validation and reading in any order, of the main arguments or parameters in a JNLP file in the form of (name,value). Examples of arguments are:
  • unnamed
  • name=value
  • name="value_with_spaces"
  • name=value_1+value_2+...+value_n
  • name="value_with_spaces_1"+"value_with_spaces_2"+...+"value_with_spaces_n"
  • --unnamed
  • --name=value
  • --name="value_with_spaces"
  • --name=value_1+value_2+...+value_n
  • --name="value_with_spaces_1"+"value_with_spaces_2"+...+"value_with_spaces_n"
  • /unnamed
  • /name=value
  • /name="value_with_spaces"
  • /name=value_1+value_2+...+value_n
  • /name="value_with_spaces_1"+"value_with_spaces_2"+...+"value_with_spaces_n"
Name-value separators can be =, : and any configured in the argument manager.

Arguments are not case sensitive.

Author:
Miquel Sas
